# PM Workspace Conventions

Stripe Accelerate PM workspace with ~30 merchant projects. Hybrid architecture: Asana for task management, local markdown for raw content.

## Structure

- `projects/active/<slug>/` — one folder per merchant (kebab-case)
  - `PROJECT.md` — overview, contacts, links, product activation
  - `action-items.md` — local backup of action items with #tags
  - `timeline.md` — chronological activity log
  - `raw/comms.md` — full email/Slack transcripts (append-only)
  - `issues/` — technical investigation notes
  - `drafts/` — email drafts with context and sources
  - `asana.json` — mapping to Asana task GID and subtask GIDs
- `sessions/` — daily session logs
- `scripts/` — automation scripts (sync-to-asana.py)
- `templates/emails/` — email templates (intro, follow-up, check-in, technical-answer, escalation)

## Asana Integration

- Each merchant = one Asana task on the "[YOUR_BOARD_NAME]" board
- Action items = Asana subtasks (name: plain action-verb description, with due date; tag lives in the Asana Tag custom field, not the name)
- **Dual-write**: always create action items in both Asana AND local `action-items.md`
- Read `asana.json` for task GID before creating subtasks
- Board sections: Discovery, Integration, Testing, Go-Live, Live, On Hold

## Rules

- Dates: always `YYYY-MM-DD`
- Folders: `kebab-case`
- Never delete project data — archive instead
- Always append to `raw/comms.md`, never overwrite
- Calendar write ops require human confirmation
- Merchant name matching: fuzzy, case-insensitive, partial
- Weekend mode: skip Gmail/Slack/Calendar fetches unless explicitly requested
